    <item>
      <title>Peanut&amp;#039;s Photo - Jeff&amp;#039;s New Horizons Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/08/15/peanuts-photo/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/08/15/peanuts-photo/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sat, 16 Aug 2025 03:45:34 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-8918" class="post-8918 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Peanut&amp;#8217;s Photo&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;On Sunday, the fireworks festival was held. It was the 2nd one of the season, but the first one that I&amp;#8217;ve participated in this year. Ankha was at the plaza (along with several other villagers), and she gave me a free sparkler, so that I could enjoy the lights in the sky &lt;em&gt;and &lt;/em&gt;in front of me.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/08/15/peanuts-photo/Array" alt="Ankha: Now you can enjoy sparkling lights in the sky about you AND right in front of you. Enjoy, I hate it!" class="wp-image-8923" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Isabelle gave me a heart bopper, so I put it on and set off my sparkler. 🎇&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/08/15/peanuts-photo/Array" alt="Setting off a sparkler in a crowded plaza during the fireworks festival." class="wp-image-8924" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;After that, I sat and enjoyed the fireworks for a few minutes.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The next day, I spotted three paper kite butterflies all flying in the same area (all on-screen at once). That&amp;#8217;s not something you see every day.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="650" height="314" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/08/15/peanuts-photo/Array" alt="Three paper kite butterflies on-screen in ACNH." class="wp-image-8919" sizes="(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;While I was chatting with Timmy in Nook&amp;#8217;s Cranny, Peanut walked by and seemingly looked right at the camera. I think she saw me! 😛&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/08/15/peanuts-photo/Array" alt="Timmy: Jeff, welcome! ...welcome!" class="wp-image-8925" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I had a camper at the campsite, and it was a villager that I was not familiar with. It was Petri the mouse!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/08/15/peanuts-photo/Array" alt="Petri, at the campsite: Well, you're not a shy one, are you? My name's Petri. How kind of you to stop by." class="wp-image-8926" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Her glasses look like they&amp;#8217;re all fogged up, and I don&amp;#8217;t know how she can even see through them. Also, the insides of her ears are different colors! One is red and one is blue; they remind me of those old 3D glasses. &lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;On Tuesday, I ran into Pascal while diving in the sea. He shared some wise words about wishing wells with me. &lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/08/15/peanuts-photo/Array" alt="Pascal: If folks make wishes at wishing wells, are they only allowed well-wishing?" class="wp-image-8927" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I spotted a banded dragonfly, and I began to chase it all over my island&amp;#8230;but I was having trouble keeping up with it. I kept losing it, then finding it, then losing it again. It took me over seven minutes, but I eventually caught it!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/08/15/peanuts-photo/Array" alt="Jeff after catching a banded dragonfly: I did it!" class="wp-image-8928" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Usually when I have &lt;em&gt;that &lt;/em&gt;much trouble with a banded dragonfly, I end up losing it for good. So I was fortunate to track it down this time. Flick was in town too, so I sold it, along with 19 other bugs from storage, to him for 109,350 bells.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Yesterday, Peanut asked if she could visit my house&amp;#8230;and I said yes. I made the right choice, because shortly after arriving at my house, she gave me a gift she picked out for me: Her photo!! Thank you, Peanut!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/08/15/peanuts-photo/Array" alt="Peanut: Peanut's photo! So YOU, right?" class="wp-image-8929" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;It&amp;#8217;s so &lt;em&gt;YOU&lt;/em&gt;, actually.&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I was thrilled to get her photo! (She&amp;#8217;s been in town about 3.5 months, if you&amp;#8217;re keeping track.) I also won an emblem blazer in a game of &amp;#8220;High Card, Low Card&amp;#8221; with her. I kept speaking to her, but she didn&amp;#8217;t want to leave&amp;#8230;and I didn&amp;#8217;t want to force her out after she just gave me her photo. So I basically just waited there for 15 minutes until she was ready to go. 😆&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Once she was gone, I added her photo to my villager photo room (it&amp;#8217;s my 25th picture). Her favorite quote on the back is &amp;#8220;Never take a nibble when you can take a bite.&amp;#8221;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/08/15/peanuts-photo/Array" alt="Peanut's photo added to my collection of villager pics." class="wp-image-8930" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I now have all of my current villagers&amp;#8217; photos. So maybe it&amp;#8217;s about time for a new villager.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Today, Katrina told me that my luck with money would improve&amp;#8230;and it was true. I got 5,000 bells from the daily glowing spot (instead of 1,000), and the money rock&amp;#8217;s 8 hits scored me 26,000 bells (instead of 16k or so).&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Bones told me that he heard I got stung by a wasp yesterday. But he reminded me that a wasp sting isn&amp;#8217;t as bad as a crocodile bite. Good point, Bones. 🐊&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/08/15/peanuts-photo/Array" alt="Bones: Man, wasp stings hurt, but not as much as crocodile bites. Life's all about perspective, at the Depot." class="wp-image-8931" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;C.J. was in town, and I caught three big-time fish in a row to complete his seasports challenge. After selling those initial catches, I grabbed 23 fish from storage. I sold them for 278,625 bells. 💰&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/08/15/peanuts-photo/Array" alt="The 23 fish I sold to C.J." class="wp-image-8932" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;See you next time! Never Stop Crossing!&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/08/15/peanuts-photo/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2025-08-15T23:45:34-04:00"&gt;August 15, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2025-08-15T23:50:12-04:00"&gt;August 15, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/ankha-lights-sm.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Irreplaceable Bucket - Jeff&amp;#039;s New Leaf Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/08/15/irreplaceable-bucket/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/08/15/irreplaceable-bucket/</guid>
      <pubDate>Fri, 15 Aug 2025 23:32:52 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-18317" class="post-18317 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Irreplaceable Bucket&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;On Sunday night, the fireworks festival was held. (This happens on every Sunday night in August, of course.) I stopped to enjoy the sights at several spots around town. Even in the low resolution of the 3DS screen, the fireworks are so pretty! 🎆&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/08/15/irreplaceable-bucket/Array" alt="The heart fireworks in Animal Crossing: New Leaf." class="wp-image-18318" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;  &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/08/15/irreplaceable-bucket/Array" alt="Fireworks appear in the sky over Forest in Animal Crossing: New Leaf." class="wp-image-18320" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Over at the event plaza, Isabelle gave me a heart bopper. I promptly put it on and posed for a photo.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/08/15/irreplaceable-bucket/Array" alt="Isabelle and Crazy Redd hanging out during the fireworks festival." class="wp-image-18321" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I also decided to buy one of Redd&amp;#8217;s cookies for 500 bells. After eating it, I found a &amp;#8220;sparkle prize&amp;#8221; inside. &lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/08/15/irreplaceable-bucket/Array" alt="Redd's Cookie: Congrats! You got a sparkle prize!" class="wp-image-18322" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I redeemed it for a miniature car. Since it came from a cookie, I guess that makes it a &lt;em&gt;sweet &lt;/em&gt;ride. 🏎️&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;On Monday, Mira asked me for a peach, and I gave her a perfect one. She rewarded me with her photo. (I&amp;#8217;ve already had one of those, but she gave me another.)&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/08/15/irreplaceable-bucket/Array" alt="Mira: Hee hee! Take my treasured Mira's pic!" class="wp-image-18323" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I also found a lost item on the ground, and I returned it to its owner, Molly. She too gave me her photo! That&amp;#8217;s two photos, both from &amp;#8220;M&amp;#8221; villagers, on the same day!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/08/15/irreplaceable-bucket/Array" alt="Molly: Thank you so much! Please take my Molly's pic as a token of my appreciation." class="wp-image-18324" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;When I played today, Cube told me that he was going to move out on the 20th. That&amp;#8217;s just five days away! I asked him to stay, but that was a fairly close call. &lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/08/15/irreplaceable-bucket/Array" alt="Cube: I'm leaving this month on the 20th. Take care, cool guy!" class="wp-image-18325" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;However, I&amp;#8217;m starting to wonder if letting him go might be the best way to get &lt;em&gt;his &lt;/em&gt;photo. He has been in town for four years now, and his photo continues to elude me. If I&amp;#8217;m feeling brave next time he asks, maybe I&amp;#8217;ll just let him go and hope he sends the photo with his goodbye letter. But for now, he&amp;#8217;s sticking around.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Inkwell told me he&amp;#8217;d like to replace his bucket with something else. I agreed to help out; I&amp;#8217;ll just add that request to my bucket list. 🪣&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/08/15/irreplaceable-bucket/Array" alt="Inkwell: I've been thinking about replacing my bucket." class="wp-image-18326" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Re-Tail didn&amp;#8217;t have anything, since &lt;em&gt;&amp;#8220;somebody&amp;#8221; &lt;/em&gt;filled up the flea market spots with gems. 😆 So I tried giving Inkwell a garden faucet that I bought from Harvey&amp;#8230;but Inkwell wouldn&amp;#8217;t accept it. He needed something that could be set on something else. So I tried giving him an eel, and that was too big.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/08/15/irreplaceable-bucket/Array" alt="Inkwell: Yikes! This is too big..." class="wp-image-18327" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I went over to T&amp;amp;T Emporium, and Tommy told me about some bargains on the top floor.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/08/15/irreplaceable-bucket/Array" alt="Tommy: Today the boutique on the top floor is having a bargain sale!" class="wp-image-18328" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;However, the shop owners have a different view of a &amp;#8220;bargain&amp;#8221; than I do. 😛&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/08/15/irreplaceable-bucket/Array" alt="Gracie: It's your lucky day! I happen to be throwing a little sale today, so I can part with this for 240,000 bells!" class="wp-image-18329" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;The middle floor didn&amp;#8217;t have any tabletop furniture either. So I decided to try a fortune cookie from the first floor. I was thinking maybe one of those Nintendo items would fit on a table. However, my cookie ticket was not a winner.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/08/15/irreplaceable-bucket/Array" alt="Today is not your day. Tomorrow doesn't look any better. (#4)" class="wp-image-18330" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Tommy gave me an electric guitar as a consolation prize, and it might sound like a decent piece of furniture. But Inkwell wouldn&amp;#8217;t accept it either, because it can&amp;#8217;t be placed on a table. Oof, this bucket is proving to be rather hard to replace!&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;So I figured I&amp;#8217;d just have to catch a fish, but a small fish. I ended up with a sweetfish, which is definitely small enough. When I went back to Inkwell&amp;#8217;s house, he seemed to be getting tired of seeing me!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/08/15/irreplaceable-bucket/Array" alt="Inkwell: Hey! Buddy! You planning on moving in or something, in ink?" class="wp-image-18331" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;However, he was (finally) happy with my gift.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/08/15/irreplaceable-bucket/Array" alt="Inkwell: Sweetfish training is something I always wanted to try! Haha! This is going to be awesome!" class="wp-image-18332" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;My reward for helping out? That bucket, of course.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/08/15/irreplaceable-bucket/Array" alt="Inkwell: Oh! I might as well give you my old bucket as a reward!" class="wp-image-18333" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Except that I don&amp;#8217;t think &lt;em&gt;I &lt;/em&gt;need a bucket either! &lt;em&gt;Hmm, what could I replace it with&amp;#8230;?&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/08/15/irreplaceable-bucket/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2025-08-15T19:32:52-04:00"&gt;August 15, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2025-08-15T19:41:41-04:00"&gt;August 15, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/20250810_HNI_0006.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
