    <item>
      <title>Mint&amp;#039;s Hand-Me-Down - Jeff&amp;#039;s ACCF Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/08/09/mints-hand-me-down/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/08/09/mints-hand-me-down/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 10 Aug 2025 03:58:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-13546" class="post-13546 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Mint&amp;#8217;s Hand-Me-Down&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;On Thursday, Biskit sent me a letter telling me he was over his cold. He sent me a caladium to thank me for the medicine I gave him last week.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;My rare catches haven&amp;#8217;t been limited to nighttime bugs; I caught a banded dragonfly in the afternoon yesterday!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/08/09/mints-hand-me-down/Array" alt="Did you see that? Did you? I caught a banded dragonfly!" class="wp-image-13551" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I spotted Saharah in town, and she was looking for old carpeting. I started asking around, and Mint was the first to give me one. But she was adamant that I shouldn&amp;#8217;t tell anyone about it for some reason.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/08/09/mints-hand-me-down/Array" alt="Mint: If word gets out, that'll be the last hand-me-down you get from me!" class="wp-image-13549" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;You know Felicity is right behind you, right?&lt;br&gt;With her big ears, you know she hears you.&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Biskit also had an old carpet to give me, and he was &lt;strong&gt;much &lt;/strong&gt;nicer about it. He was very happy to be able to help out!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/08/09/mints-hand-me-down/Array" alt="Biskit: Isn't it funny how old carpets make you, me, and Saharah all happy? It's like they're magic carpets!" class="wp-image-13550" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;None of my other villagers were able to help out, though. Fortunately, I had an old flooring in storage. I took the three of them over to Saharah, and she gave me a concrete floor in return. That&amp;#8217;s always a hard thing to accept.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;I played last night to hunt some bugs, and Marina asked me for a new catchphrase. I told her to say &amp;#8220;I&amp;#8217;m afraid,&amp;#8221; although I&amp;#8217;m not yet sure how this will work out. Hopefully she&amp;#8217;ll use it in some funny ways in the coming weeks.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/08/09/mints-hand-me-down/Array" alt="Marina: ...It's decided, then! From now on, I'm going to say I'm afraid!" class="wp-image-13552" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Monty wanted to trade a skull shirt for my fruit beetle, and I agreed to the trade. I don&amp;#8217;t care about fruit beetles. But his catchphrase made it sound like he was handing me his poop. 💩&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="499" height="280" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/08/09/mints-hand-me-down/Array" alt="Monty: OK, first things first. Take this off my hands, it's pooop!" class="wp-image-13547" sizes="auto, (max-width: 499px) 100vw, 499px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;On second thought, you can keep it.&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Today, I gave out another new catchphrase, this time to Felicity. I told her to say &amp;#8220;in my tea.&amp;#8221; We&amp;#8217;ll have to wait and &lt;em&gt;tea&lt;/em&gt; how that one turns out too.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Later on, I attended K.K. Slider&amp;#8217;s concert at the Roost. I asked for a random song, and he performed &amp;#8220;K.K. Mambo&amp;#8221; for me. It may not be one of the more popular songs, but it&amp;#8217;s a pretty good song.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/08/09/mints-hand-me-down/Array" alt="K.K.: All right, get ready to dig the riffs on this ditty: K.K. Mambo." class="wp-image-13553" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I found a doghouse in the recycle bin at town hall. Even though it looked a bit &lt;em&gt;ruff&lt;/em&gt;, I took it so I can give it a new &lt;em&gt;leash &lt;/em&gt;on life. 🐶&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;I went on another late-night bug hunt tonight, but it was a relatively short session (at least compared my other ones lately). But I still made about 170k on the night. There&amp;#8217;s still three weeks to go in peak bug season, and I&amp;#8217;ll have to go on a bug hunt during a fireworks festival this month. It may not be this weekend, though.&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/08/09/mints-hand-me-down/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2025-08-09T23:58:00-04:00"&gt;August 9, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2025-08-10T02:22:45-04:00"&gt;August 10, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/RUU_8303-sm.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Sparkler Season - Jeff&amp;#039;s New Horizons Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/08/09/sparkler-season/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/08/09/sparkler-season/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 10 Aug 2025 01:12:39 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-8906" class="post-8906 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Sparkler Season&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;Last Saturday, Sydney the koala was camping at the campsite. I&amp;#8217; ve had her in my GameCube town practically forever, but I don&amp;#8217;t particularly feel the need to add her to my New Horizons island.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/08/09/sparkler-season/Array" alt="Sydney, at the campsite: All the fresh air and open sky here is waking my inner poet, sunshine." class="wp-image-8910" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;However, I did opt to play a game with her&amp;#8230;and I lost. No prize for me.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;The next day, I visited June. She told me she was going to start charging me one bell to relax in her house! 😉&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/08/09/sparkler-season/Array" alt="June: Doesn't time spent relaxing at home fill you with joy? I'd love for you to relax here as well, for 1 bell." class="wp-image-8911" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;At least it&amp;#8217;s affordable. She only charges the &lt;em&gt;bear &lt;/em&gt;minimum. 🐻&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Forest&amp;#8217;s birthday season kept rolling on, with Bones celebrating a birthday on Monday (August 4th). I gave him a smoker that I bought at the shop, and he seemed thrilled!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/08/09/sparkler-season/Array" alt="Bones, at his birthday party: Whoa! I-- You-- What?! A smoker?! Are you SURE I can have this?!" class="wp-image-8912" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Bone appétit!&lt;/em&gt; Ketchup was also at the party &lt;s&gt;and on the menu&lt;/s&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Over at the Resident Services plaza, I found June, Bob, and Louie setting off some sparklers. 🎇&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/08/09/sparkler-season/Array" alt="June, Bob, and Louie set off some sparklers in Animal Crossing: New Horizons." class="wp-image-8913" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I ran into Pascal on Tuesday, and he said you need to pick a direction to get ahead in life. Sometimes that&amp;#8217;s the hardest part!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/08/09/sparkler-season/Array" alt="Pascal: If you wanna get ahead in life, you gotta pick a direction first, maaan!" class="wp-image-8914" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;After selling some stuff yesterday, my bank account balance reached a new milestone: 120 million bells.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/08/09/sparkler-season/Array" alt="Savings Balance: 120,000,000 bells." class="wp-image-8915" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;My New Leaf savings balance is still larger (135 million), but New Horizons is slowly catching up. It&amp;#8217;ll overtake New Leaf eventually, but it may take another year or more.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Tonight, K.K. Slider was in town and he performed &amp;#8220;K.K. Aria&amp;#8221; for me and Static.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="550" height="347" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/08/09/sparkler-season/Array" alt="K.K. Slider performs for Static and Jeff." class="wp-image-8916" sizes="auto, (max-width: 550px) 100vw, 550px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Here are a few other quick notes about the past week in Forest:&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;ul class="wp-block-list"&gt; &lt;li&gt;Last Saturday, Gulliver sent me an alpinist hat.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;K.K. performed &amp;#8220;K.K. Sonata&amp;#8221; for me, Bob, Louie, Static, and Agent S.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;On Wednesday, I sold 32 bugs to Flick for 243,000 bells.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;Yesterday, Gullivarrr sent me some pirate boots.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;    &lt;p&gt;I posted my latest New Horizons Moments video earlier today, so I hope you&amp;#8217;ll check it out.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio"&gt;&lt;div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper"&gt; &lt;iframe loading="lazy" title="New Horizons Moments #35 (Animal Crossing ACNH)" width="660" height="371" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/27K0nVkbiv8?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;/figure&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/08/09/sparkler-season/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published updated" datetime="2025-08-09T21:12:39-04:00"&gt;August 9, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/sydney-camper-sm.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>First Rainbow! - Jeff&amp;#039;s ACWW Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/08/07/first-rainbow/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/08/07/first-rainbow/</guid>
      <pubDate>Fri, 08 Aug 2025 00:29:41 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-8294" class="post-8294 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;First Rainbow!&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	 	 	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;It was raining in town yesterday, and Truffles told me that she&amp;#8217;s not into water polo when it rains. That seemed like a weird thing to say, because she&amp;#8217;s not into water polo anyway. But I&amp;#8217;d think the rain wouldn&amp;#8217;t bother you as much when you&amp;#8217;re already wet. 🤷&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/08/07/first-rainbow/Array" alt="Truffles: Helloooooo! Know what? When it's raining, I'm just not into water polo..." class="wp-image-8296" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Whitney told me that her favorite thing about catching bugs is the bugs&amp;#8217; sound of defeat when she catches them. &lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/08/07/first-rainbow/Array" alt="Whitney: What I like best about bug catching is the sound of defeat it makes when I win." class="wp-image-8297" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I don&amp;#8217;t know what to make of that. My villagers are weird.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Pippy wanted to have a contest to see who could catch a horse mackerel first, but the joke was on her&amp;#8230;because I already had one.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/08/07/first-rainbow/Array" alt="Pippy: So, you gave me your horse mackerel, in a pond!" class="wp-image-8298" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I gave it to her, and she rewarded me with a pastel dot wall.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Drift has still been sick with a cold this week, so I gave him some medicine yesterday and again today.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/08/07/first-rainbow/Array" alt="Drift: I live again! YESSSSSS!" class="wp-image-8295" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;When I started up the game today, I was met with quite a surprise: A rainbow!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="298" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/08/07/first-rainbow/Array" alt="A rainbow appears in the sky in Animal Crossing: Wild World (ACWW)." class="wp-image-8300" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;This was my first time seeing a rainbow in Wild World! I have now seen a rainbow in Wild World, &lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acblog/2011/09/09/rainbow/"&gt;GameCube&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2013/07/07/first-rainbow/"&gt;New Leaf&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2024/07/20/first-rainbow/"&gt;New Horizons&lt;/a&gt;. But apparently I haven&amp;#8217;t seen one in City Folk yet, as hard as that is to believe! At least I can&amp;#8217;t find any screenshots of it, or mentions of it in my blog!&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;At any rate, I changed the Virtual Console screen settings to view this rainbow in standard DS mode as well:&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="550" height="533" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/08/07/first-rainbow/Array" alt="A rainbow in Animal Crossing: Wild World." class="wp-image-8301" sizes="auto, (max-width: 550px) 85vw, 550px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;The rainbow gradually faded as I played. I&amp;#8217;m not sure if I got to see it at its peak or not, since it was already underway when I started up the game. But it was nice to finally see it in this game!&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Anyway, Saharah was in town today, and she asked me to make some deliveries for her. I took carpet packages over to Mabel and Pelly for her. She rewarded me with an ancient wall.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/08/07/first-rainbow/Array" alt="Saharah: Done! It is finally done! Thank you so much for your help, friend!" class="wp-image-8302" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Right after the rainbow vanished completely, I spotted a balloon present overhead. I shot it down, and I found a clothesline pole inside.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;I listened in on a conversation between Pippy and Curt, and Pippy was singing a song. 🎶&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/08/07/first-rainbow/Array" alt="Pippy: I love puppies! I love candy!" class="wp-image-8304" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;  &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/08/07/first-rainbow/Array" alt="Pippy: (Maybe a little more than) I LOVE YOU!" class="wp-image-8305" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;But Curt was definitely not a fan. 😆&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/08/07/first-rainbow/Array" alt="Curt: Ha! Laaaaaame! That song is lamer than a llama!" class="wp-image-8306" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Pippy replied that the song was popular with the girls in town, and they both insulted each other&amp;#8217;s taste in music. But the conversation left them both feeling depressed.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/08/07/first-rainbow/Array" alt="Pippy: Believe it or not, it's hard work being so chipper... And I'm overworked." class="wp-image-8307" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;img alt='' src='https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/08/07/first-rainbow/Array' class='avatar avatar-49 photo' height='49' width='49'/&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/08/07/first-rainbow/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2025-08-07T20:29:41-04:00"&gt;August 7, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2025-08-07T20:44:01-04:00"&gt;August 7, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt; &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/08/truffles-polo.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
